                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1900.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Adee directs Mr. Goodnow to immediately forward to Minister Conger the
                    following cipher message:</p>
                <p>August 10, morning. Receipt of Mr. Conger’s cipher telegram, identical with
                    telegrams of French and other ministers, is acknowledged; his determination not
                    to accept Chinese escort is approved. This determination has been communicated
                    to Chinese Government and their cooperation with relief expedition which
                    captured Yangtsu on August 6 has been urged.</p>
                <p>Dispatches in cipher should be dated.)</p>
            </div>
